nerot.spring
Class HttpGetCronScheduler

java.lang.Object
  nerot.spring.HttpGetCronScheduler
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean
public class HttpGetCronScheduler
extends Object
implements org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean

This bean lets you schedule Nerot by just defining a bean (e.g. in the root context of your application). The properties that must be set on the bean are the same as the ones on the corresponding schedule method in Nerot:

nerot.scheduleHttpGet(url, cronSchedule);

The following are properties that must be set on this bean:
  • url
  • cronSchedule
It also has a "nerot" property, but that is @Autowired.

(See the corresponding schedule method in Nerot for more details on the types and functions of that method.)
